  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN174.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">pācaṟaikkaṭ ṭalaimakaṉ taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What HE said to his heart in the war camp.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN174.2">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>iruperu vēntar māṟukoḷ viyaṉkaḷat</l>
        <l>torupaṭai koṇṭu varupaṭai peyarkkuñ</l>
        <l>celva muṭaiyōrkku niṉṟaṉṟu viṟaleṉap</l>
        <l>pūkkō ḷēya taṇṇumai vilakkic</l>
        <l>celvē māta laṟiyāṇ mullai</l>
        <l>nērkāṉ mutukoṭi kuḻaippa nīrcorinta</l>
        <l>kālai vāṉattuk kaṭuṅkuraṟ koṇmū</l>
        <l>muḻaṅkutoṟu kaiyaṟ ṟiraṅkinap pulantu</l>
        <l>paḻaṅkaṇ koṇṭa pacalai mēṉiyaḷ</l>
        <l>yāṅkā kuvaḷko ṟāṉē vēṅkai</l>
        <l>yūḻuṟu kiḷarvī kaṭuppak kē<supplied>ḻ</supplied>koḷa</l>
        <l>vākat tarumpiya mācaṟu cuṇaṅki</l>
        <l>ṉaṉmaṇal viyaliṭa naṭanta</l>
        <l>ciṉmel lotu<supplied>kkiṉ māa yōḷē</supplied>.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>She who didn’t know that we would go, (5)</l>
        <l>checking the Taṇṇumai drum, while flower clusters meet(?),(4)</l>
        <l>[thinking] that on the wide battlefield where two great kings oppose each other, (1)</l>
        <l>the victory is permanent for those who possess wealth, (3)</l>
        <l>when the coming weapon takes [and] removes the one weapon, (2)</l>
        <l>she with a body [full of] the pallor brought by distress, (9)</l>
        <l>vexed with us, desolately aggrieved with every thunder[-clap] (8)</l>
        <l>from fierce-voiced clouds in the sky at a time (7)</l>
        <l>when water poured forth, for the fine-stemmed old creepers to sprout (6)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">on the jasmine, (5d)</l>
        <l>what will become of her, herself, (10a-c)</l>
        <l>– the dark one with few soft steps (14)</l>
        <l>who walked the wide place of good sand, (13)</l>
        <l>with flawless beauty-spots that budded on [her] bosom (12)</l>
        <l>so as to bring luster, resembling ripe shining kino blossoms? (10d-11)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
